    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to compare the effects of Azor (a combination of amlodipine and
      olmesartan) with Hyzaar ( a combination of losartan and hydrochlorothiazide) on the thin
      lining on the inside of blood vessels. These cells help keep blood vessels healthy and blood
      pressure normal.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Participants must be 18-75 years of age, African American, and have a combination of high
      blood pressure, insulin resistance (Type 2 Diabetes), low HDL cholesterol levels or obesity.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
